{
  "texts": [
    "BackgroundHealthy People 2030 vision calls for a \"society in which all people can achieve their full potential for health and wellbeing\" [1].",
    "This vision is aspirational and leaves much to be done.",
    "Among high-income countries, the average number of annual deaths that could be avoided altogether with preventive or treatment strategies ranges from 130 to more than 330 per 100,000 people [2].",
    "Although the lag time from knowledge generation to translation varies by situation, recent estimates suggest the average time is 15 years, which is a modest improvement from prior estimates [3,4].",
    "To move the needle and make real progress toward this vision, we need to do better faster, which includes producing and sustaining equitable results."
  ]
}